          <div class="main_blog_details">
			<a href="#"><h4>Mackay came to Taiwan and encountered difficulties</h4></a>
			  
			<!-- CC3.0 Picture -->
			<center><img class="img-fluid" src="../../img/paint/S_tooth.png" alt=""></center>
		    <input2big>
			  <h2>【Preamble】</h2>
              　　When Mackay was 26, he finally came to Taiwan  to preach. He loved Taiwan so much that he overcame the language barrier and  learned Taiwanese in just 5 months and even set up the first church in Tamsui.  Even though he faced obstructions from local people, he found a way to preach  through medical works. He established the Hobe Mackay Medical Center and helped  with dental works and treating Malaria, successfully started his preaching  journey, and later established 60 churches in total. <br>
              <br>
              　　Mackay&rsquo;s secret  in preaching was to constantly travel, his footprint spread over half of the  island. After staying in Tamsui for a while, he started his discovery journey  in the Northern Taiwan region, reaching as far as Puli and Sun Moon Lake. Then  he climbed the Snow Mountain twice in a year, went deep into the southern  native tribes, and even went to Hualien multiple times. He also sailed to  Pengjiayu, Cotton Isle, Vase Island, and even set up a church on Guishan  Island. These spots were rarely visited by missionaries. He always walks on  foot when he led his students to meetings in Southern Taiwan. <br>
                <br>
              　　After Mackay settled in Tamsui, he learned  Taiwanese and Mandarin actively. Using his outstanding speaking skills to make  the teachings easy to understand, he slowly began to overcome the oppositions  and gain more and more followers. Other than the missionary works, he also  taught students Latin characters, Astronomy, Geography, Medical, and other  western knowledge, training the next generation of missionaries. <br><br>
              　　Dr.James Laidlaw Maxwell  arrived in Takao (present-day Kaohsiung) and later went into Tainan to start  his medical and missionary works. He would prescribe medicines for people after  preaching, the process was extremely difficult. He was forced to go to Fengshan  Chihou after local oppositions. He later established the first western hospital  in Taiwan and set up chapels across southern Taiwan.<br>
              <br>
              <h2><strong>【</strong><strong>Solutions</strong><strong>】</strong><strong> </strong></h2>
            　　In order to interact with Tamsui residents  more smoothly, he found a cowboy and learned Taiwanese from him. After  practicing for 5 months, he finally went on stage to preach. <br>
            <br>
              　　Mackay  used his extraordinary abilities to rebuild the churches destroyed by the  Japanese army and saved many Christian suffering from the attack. He stated the  situation to Nogi Maresuke and Kodama Gentaro, the then government leader, and  received protection for all Christians. <br>
                <br>
              　　In the early years of the Japanese Occupation,  Mackay helped Japanese missionaries to establish churches in Taiwan and  preached to Japanese people. He developed friendships with them and this helped  him with his missionary work later under Japanese Occupation.<br>
		    </input2big>
